      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just \"advanced cognitive abilities\" though. it feels like it's happening in my head too, like i'm picking up on the frequency of the signals. when they do that specific spiral near the fountain, i get this sudden feeling in my chest that the pressure is about to shift. it's like i'm tapped into their network. can you look into if there's any biological reason why a human might be able to interpret these specific avian frequency shifts? i feel like i'm not just guessing anymore, i'm actually reading them.",
